<subSubSection id="F0DE654CFF8D672200A42134FD36F9BB" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF8D672200A42134FC95FB96" blockId="57.[151,824,1008,1063]" box="[151,824,1039,1063]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672200A42134FE80FB96" bold="true" box="[151,301,1039,1063]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<typeStatus id="677F8865FF8D672200A42134FF62FB96" box="[151,207,1039,1063]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D67220100212BFC9EFB96" authority="Maskell 1890: 143 - 144" authorityName="Maskell" authorityPageNumber="143 - 144" authorityYear="1890" box="[307,819,1040,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Rhizococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchellus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D67220100212BFD80FB96" box="[307,557,1040,1063]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Rhizococcus pulchellus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8D67220200212BFC9EFB96" author="Maskell, W. M." box="[563,819,1040,1063]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="133 - 156" refId="ref51133" refString="Maskell, W. M. 1890 (1889). Further notes on Coccidae, with descriptions of new species from Australia, Fiji, and New Zealand. Transactions and Proceedings of the New Zealand Institute, 22, 133 - 156." type="journal article" year="1890">Maskell 1890: 143–144</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF8D672200A4216EFD7FFA55" blockId="57.[151,1437,1109,2031]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672200A4216EFD9DFBDE" bold="true" box="[151,560,1109,1135]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Generic diagnosis. Adult female.</emphasis>
Body variable in shape; anal lobes variable but all with 3 dorsal setae, an apical seta and a ventral seta. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672201C02140FDFDFB25" box="[499,592,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Dorsum</emphasis>
. Dorsal derm usually nodulose; setae variable, ranging from minute and digitate to enlarged and spinose. Macrotubular ducts present or absent; when present variable in structure. Microtubular ducts small, generally with 1–5 at base of enlarged dorsal setae. Loculate pores generally absent. Cruciform pores absent. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672201F121D0FD8EFAB5" box="[450,547,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Margin.</emphasis>
With or without marginal setal fringe. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672203CE21D0FBFFFAB5" box="[1021,1106,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Venter.</emphasis>
Setae flagellate or spinose. Suranal setae spatulate on most species. Macrotubular ducts present or absent. Microtubular ducts present along margin or absent. Loculate pores, each with 3 or 5 loculi, present on abdomen. Anal ring well developed, with pores and 3 or 4 pairs of setae. Antennae 6 or 7 segmented. Frontal lobes perhaps absent but antennal tubercles sometimes present. Labium either 3 segmented or composed of 2 fused segments. Metathoracic coxae, femur and tibia often with translucent pores. Vulva present between abdominal segments VII and VIII. (Modified after 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8D672201C320F1FD68FA55" author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G." box="[496,709,1482,1508]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="365 - 405" refId="ref49693" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J., Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G. (2008) Relationships among felt scale insects (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) of southern beech, Nothofagus (Nothofagaceae), with first descriptions of Australian species on the Nothofagus - feeding genus Madarococcus Hoy. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 365 - 405." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D6722027320F0FD2DFA55" box="[576,640,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al.,</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF8D672200F520CBFD36F9BB" blockId="57.[151,1437,1109,2031]" box="[198,667,1520,1546]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Apparently restricted to 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672201D720CBFD35F9BB" authorityName="Kuprianova" authorityYear="1962" box="[484,664,1520,1546]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Nothofagaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F0DE654CFF8D672100F5232EFB5EFD26" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF8D672200F5232EFAA5F885" blockId="57.[151,1437,1109,2031]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672200F5232EFEE4F99E" bold="true" box="[198,329,1557,1583]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Comment.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672201D9232EFD3AF99F" authorityName="Hoy" authorityYear="1962" box="[490,663,1557,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672201D9232EFD3AF99F" box="[490,663,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Madarococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has recently been revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8D67220410232EFAB1F99E" author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G." box="[1059,1308,1557,1583]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="365 - 405" refId="ref49693" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J., Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G. (2008) Relationships among felt scale insects (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) of southern beech, Nothofagus (Nothofagaceae), with first descriptions of Australian species on the Nothofagus - feeding genus Madarococcus Hoy. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 365 - 405." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D6722044F232EFB12F99F" box="[1148,1215,1557,1582]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
based on nucleotide sequence data and morphology. As part of this review, they transferred 4 South American species previously included in 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D6722019A235BFD83F9C8" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[425,558,1632,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D6722019A235BFD83F9C8" box="[425,558,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D67220266235BFCAEF9C8" authorityName="Hoy" authorityYear="1962" box="[597,771,1632,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D67220266235BFCAEF9C8" box="[597,771,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Madarococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D67220341235BFB5AF9CB" authority="Miller and Gonzalez" authorityName="Miller and Gonzalez" box="[882,1271,1632,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D67220341235BFC57F9C8" box="[882,1018,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. chilensis</emphasis>
Miller and González
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D67220578235BFA22F9CB" box="[1355,1423,1632,1658]" name="Chile" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Chile</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672200A423BEFD86F92E" authority="Miller and Gonzalez" authorityName="Miller and Gonzalez" box="[151,555,1669,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eurythrix">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672200A423BEFE8AF92F" box="[151,295,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. eurythrix</emphasis>
Miller and González
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D672202B223BEFD54F92E" box="[641,761,1669,1695]" name="Argentina" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D6722030523BEFCD1F92E" box="[822,892,1669,1695]" name="Chile" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Chile</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672203A123BEFB34F92E" authority="Hoy" authorityName="Hoy" authorityYear="1962" box="[914,1177,1669,1695]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="navarinoensis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672203A123BEFBF0F92F" box="[914,1117,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. navarinoensis</emphasis>
Hoy
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D672204C323BEFAC5F92E" box="[1264,1384,1669,1695]" name="Argentina" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D672200A42391FF76F975" box="[151,219,1706,1732]" name="Chile" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Chile</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672201122390FD4BF975" authority="Miller and Gonzalez" authorityName="Miller and Gonzalez" box="[289,742,1706,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhadinothrix">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672201122390FE72F975" box="[289,479,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. rhadinothrix</emphasis>
Miller and González
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D6722030D2391FC2BF975" box="[830,902,1706,1732]" name="Chile" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Chile</collectingCountry>
). All of these species are known only from 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672200A423EBFE8FF958" box="[151,290,1744,1769]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672200A423EBFE8FF958" box="[151,290,1744,1769]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Nothofagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D6722010123EBFE42F95B" authorityName="Kuprianova" authorityYear="1962" box="[306,495,1744,1770]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Nothofagaceae</taxonomicName>
). We suspect that 1 of the species recently described by González (
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8D6722051223EBFF4AF8BE" author="Gonzalez" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="50 - 56" refId="ref49077" refString="Gonzalez. P. (2008 a) Two new species of Eriococcus (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) from the Andino Patagonica region of Argentina, with a key to the Eriococcus species of that region. Zootaxa, 1899, 50 - 56." type="journal article" year="2008">González, 2008a</bibRefCitation>
) from 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D6722017023CEFE6EF8BE" box="[323,451,1781,1807]" name="Argentina" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Argentina</collectingCountry>
on 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672201CB23CEFD21F8BF" box="[504,652,1781,1806]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" genus="Nothofagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672201CB23CEFD21F8BF" box="[504,652,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Nothofagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D6722029123CEFC07F8BF" box="[674,938,1781,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dombeyi">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D6722029123CEFC07F8BF" box="[674,938,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Eriococcus dombeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) will eventually also be transfered to 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672200A42220FEE9F885" authorityName="Hoy" authorityYear="1962" box="[151,324,1819,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672200A42220FEE9F885" box="[151,324,1819,1844]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Madarococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hardy 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672201902220FE73F885" box="[419,478,1819,1844]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
also included species in this genus from 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D6722038C2221FBF6F885" box="[959,1115,1818,1844]" name="New Zealand" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="C0D37657FF8D672204A62221FAA9F885" box="[1173,1284,1818,1844]" name="Australia" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Australia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF8D672100F5227BFCC8FF66" blockId="57.[151,1437,1109,2031]" lastBlockId="58.[151,1436,152,663]" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Recent molecular data have demonstrated that previous concepts of genera such as 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672204D0227BFDE1F8CF" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672204D0227BFA3AF8E8" box="[1251,1431,1856,1881]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">Acanthococcus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672200A4225EFE89F8CF" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,292,1893,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eriococcus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D67220101225EFDE1F8CF" authority=", Greenisca" authorityName="Greenisca" box="[306,588,1893,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Gossyparia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gossyparia, Greenisca</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D6722026E225EFD52F8CF" box="[605,767,1893,1918]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D6722026E225EFD54F8CF" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1875" box="[605,761,1893,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Rhizococcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rhizococcus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
etc. need careful re-analysis, because species that are similar morphologically differ considerably using molecular characters (
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8D672203DD22B1FB59F815" author="Cook, L. G. &amp; Gullan, P. J." box="[1006,1268,1930,1956]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="441 - 452" refId="ref48753" refString="Cook, L. G. &amp; Gullan, P. J. (2004) The gall-inducing habit has evolved multiple times among the eriococcid scale insects (Sternorrhyncha: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae). Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 83, 441 - 452." type="journal article" year="2004">Cook &amp; Gullan, 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8D6722053222B1FF78F87B" author="Kondo, T. &amp; Hardy, N. &amp; Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P." pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref50582" refString="Kondo, T., Hardy, N., Cook, L. &amp; Gullan, P. (2006) Description of two new genera and species of Eriococcidae (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) from southern South America. Zootaxa, 1349, 19 - 36." type="journal article" year="2006">
Kondo 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D6722056A22B0FA20F815" box="[1369,1421,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8D672200D1228BFE13F87B" author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G." box="[226,446,1968,1994]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="365 - 405" refId="ref49693" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J., Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G. (2008) Relationships among felt scale insects (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) of southern beech, Nothofagus (Nothofagaceae), with first descriptions of Australian species on the Nothofagus - feeding genus Madarococcus Hoy. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 365 - 405." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D67220100228BFEC5F878" box="[307,360,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al</emphasis>
., 2008
</bibRefCitation>
). The lack of diagnostic morphological characters for characterizing 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8D672204DD228BFE28F85E" authority="(Hardy et al., 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Hardy" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672204DD228BFA36F878" box="[1262,1435,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Madarococcus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8D672200AC22EEFED0F85E" author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G." box="[159,381,2005,2031]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="365 - 405" refId="ref49693" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J., Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G. (2008) Relationships among felt scale insects (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) of southern beech, Nothofagus (Nothofagaceae), with first descriptions of Australian species on the Nothofagus - feeding genus Madarococcus Hoy. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 365 - 405." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8D672200C722EEFE84F85F" box="[244,297,2005,2030]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al</emphasis>
., 2008
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
adds further confusion to the status of these genera. Until more definitive analyses are undertaken, we will adhere to the current classification except where more detailed analyses have been undertaken, as is the case in the paper by 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8E6721024E2586FCCCFF66" author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G." box="[637,865,189,215]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="365 - 405" refId="ref49693" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J., Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G. (2008) Relationships among felt scale insects (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) of southern beech, Nothofagus (Nothofagaceae), with first descriptions of Australian species on the Nothofagus - feeding genus Madarococcus Hoy. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 365 - 405." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672102FD2586FCACFF67" box="[718,769,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF8E672100F525D9FB5EFD26" blockId="58.[151,1436,152,663]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
We note, however, that 3 of the 4 South American 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E6721037A25D9FBFAFF4D" box="[841,1111,226,252]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E6721037A25D9FC5BFF4A" box="[841,1014,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Madarococcus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
mentioned above, i.e., 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E6721054F25D9FE5CFE90" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E6721054F25D9FEABFE90" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">M. chilensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672101202433FE41FE90" authorityName="Hoy" authorityYear="1962" box="[275,492,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="navarinoensis">M. navarinoensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E6721021C2433FD5FFE90" box="[559,754,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhadinothrix">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E6721021C2433FD5FFE90" box="[559,754,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. rhadinothrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could just as easily be placed in a taxon separate from 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672100A42416FEE8FEF7" box="[151,325,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672100A42416FEE8FEF7" box="[151,325,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Madarococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the morphological phylogeny of 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8E672103772416FB81FEF6" author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G." box="[836,1068,301,327]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="365 - 405" refId="ref49693" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J., Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G. (2008) Relationships among felt scale insects (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) of southern beech, Nothofagus (Nothofagaceae), with first descriptions of Australian species on the Nothofagus - feeding genus Madarococcus Hoy. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 365 - 405." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672103A52416FC66FEF7" box="[918,971,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, with only 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672104812416FAEBFEF7" box="[1202,1350,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eurythrix">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672104812416FAEBFEF7" box="[1202,1350,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. eurythrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
placed outside of the lineage, separated by 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E6721027C2469FC44FEDD" authority="Hardy &amp; Gullan. The" authorityName="Hardy &amp; Gullan. The" box="[591,1001,338,364]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occultus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E6721027C2469FD71FEDA" box="[591,732,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. occultus</emphasis>
Hardy &amp; Gullan. The
</taxonomicName>
molecular phylogeny could also be interpreted so that the South American species of “ 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672102DB2443FC08FE20" box="[744,933,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672102DB2443FC36FE20" box="[744,923,376,401]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Madarococcus</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
would be placed in a separate taxon, but in this case 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E6721013024A6FE3BFE07" box="[259,406,413,438]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eurythrix">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E6721013024A6FE3BFE07" box="[259,406,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. eurythrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672101E224A6FD31FE07" authorityName="Hoy" authorityYear="1962" box="[465,668,413,438]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="navarinoensis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672101E224A6FD31FE07" box="[465,668,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. navarinoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would be included. Apparently, no specimens of 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672104D524A6FE9BFE6A" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672104D524A6FADAFE07" box="[1254,1399,413,438]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chilensis">M. chilensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672105B724A6FE9BFE6A" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhadinothrix">M rhadinothrix</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, or 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E6721015F24F9FDADFE6A" box="[364,512,450,475]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occultus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E6721015F24F9FDADFE6A" box="[364,512,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">M. occultus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were available for DNA analysis. 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF8E672103F324F9FB1BFE6D" author="Hardy, N. B. &amp; Gullan, P. J. &amp; Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G." box="[960,1206,450,476]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="365 - 405" refId="ref49693" refString="Hardy, N. B., Gullan, P. J., Henderson, R. C. &amp; Cook, L. G. (2008) Relationships among felt scale insects (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) of southern beech, Nothofagus (Nothofagaceae), with first descriptions of Australian species on the Nothofagus - feeding genus Madarococcus Hoy. Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 365 - 405." type="journal article" year="2008">
Hardy 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E6721042B24F9FBFDFE6A" box="[1048,1104,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
point out that the morphological, DNA, and combined morphological and DNA trees are variable in the placement and support of the South American 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672101992736FD16FD96" box="[426,699,525,551]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672101992736FDFAFD97" box="[426,599,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Madarococcus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
Their classification strategy was to minimize disruption to the generally accepted system and still be consistent with their phylogenetic results, but this has left a lack of diagnostic morphological characters for characterizing 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E6721032F2763FC64FDC0" box="[796,969,600,625]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E6721032F2763FC64FDC0" box="[796,969,600,625]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Madarococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It appears that more research is needed to clearly understand the species composition of 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF8E672102E02746FC2DFD27" box="[723,896,637,662]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Madarococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF8E672102E02746FC2DFD27" box="[723,896,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Madarococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly in South America.
</paragraph>
